# Team Tools

The intended readership of this page is new joiners to the team, the page illustrates tools which the team use frequently.

### MacOS

Engineers will be provided with MacBooks.
Some additional software and commandline tools are subsequently required, they can be quickly installed following these instructions.

### VSCode

Some of our preferred extensions are listed below, to install these extensions on VSCode (_Ctrl + Shift + P; "Install Extensions"_):

- [HashiCorp Terraform](https://marketplace.visualstudio.com/items?itemName=HashiCorp.terraform) (Syntax highlighting and autocompletion for Terraform)

- [Gitmoji](https://marketplace.visualstudio.com/items?itemName=seatonjiang.gitmoji-vscode) 😎 (An emoji tool for your git commit messages)

- [Tabnine](https://marketplace.visualstudio.com/items?itemName=TabNine.tabnine-vscode) (👩‍💻🤖 JavaScript, Python, Java, Typescript & all other languages - AI Code completion plugin. Tabnine makes developers more productive by auto-completing their code.)

- (optional) Change your colour scheme. Save your eyes! 👀
  [Dracula](https://marketplace.visualstudio.com/items?itemName=dracula-theme.theme-dracula) 🧛 is a good one.

### Signing GitHub Commits
Some of our repos are configured to accept only signed commits.